data.description: ***With a full list price offer, Seller will grant a $5,000 credit at closing for a 2-1 RATE BUYDOWN... OR $5,000 credit towards BUYERS CLOSING COSTS at closing.*** This incredible 3-story home has tons of charm and was actually the first ever B&B in the town of Shenandoah and originally named "Strickler's Modern Rooms for Tourists." It can be converted back to a B&B or it can be used as a short term rental with a business license! This gorgeous brick home hosts 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 2,600+ above grade sq ft, PLUS a huge unfinished 1,350 sq foot basement for ample storage space. Gorgeous hardwood floors and crown molding run throughout main floor and into the primary suite with its full bathroom. The upstairs space has 3 large bedrooms, a nicely updated guest bathroom, a bonus room, and a huge hallway with a small alcove that would be perfect for a office or library.  Sit out on the back screened in porch and enjoy this unique property with amazing Massanutten Mountain views, with great location close to everything you need and more! It has been incredibly maintained over the years and is ready for its next owner! The building in the back is not in good condition and no value is given to it for the current price.
